channel.title: Time of your life tab
channel.description:
This is a nice and easy way of playing Time of your life(Good Riddance) by Green Day.
In my opinion this is V easy to learn.
Recommendations: A tuned Acoustic guitar. A pick(this is ++++) Willing to learn.
This is to be played twice: E|------------------| B|-------3----------| G|----0-----0----0-| D|-------------0---| A|-----------------| E|-3---------------|
This is to played Once: E|------------------| B|-------3----------| G|----0-----0----0-| D|-------------0---| A|-3---------------| E|-----------------|
This is to played Once: E|------------------| B|-------3----------| G|----2-----2----2-| D|-0-----------0---| A|----------------| E|-----------------|
And then play the first bit again.
This was the first song i ever learnt =]
Just the clear things up: [quote="Davidude"][quote author=I Samn I link=topic=340239.msg2636459#msg2636459 date=1232565497] This is to be played twice: E|------------------| B|-------3----------| G|----0-----0----0-| D|-------------0---| A|-----------------| E|-3---------------|
This is to played Once: E|------------------| B|-------3----------| G|----0-----0----0-| D|-------------0---| A|-3---------------| E|-----------------|
[/quote] Why didn't you just say to do this 3 times? Or was that a mistake that both of those are the same?[/quote]
No mistake, you just move your finger down from the E string to the A string. When you play it and you've heard the song before you'll realise. But yeah that sounds like its going to be a recuuring question.
